 by the CIA, the forging of regional political alliances, and the import of popular cultures from around the world. Klein combines nuanced readings of Han's sophisticated style with careful attention to key issues of modernity-such as feminism, cosmopolitanism, and consumerism-in the first monograph devoted to this major Korean director. A free open access ebook is available upon publication. Learn more at www.luminosoa.org.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCommunication. Mass media. 0aHistory of Asia. 0aMotion picture producers and directorszKorea (South) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszKorea (South). 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspectszKorea. 0aMotion pictureszKoreaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  a1950s.  aaesthetic.  aasia.  acia.  aconsumerism.  acosmopolitanism.  acultural cold war.  afeminism.  afilm culture.  afilm style.  aglamorous.  agolden age cinemas.  ahan hyung mo.  ajapanese colonialism.  amadame freedom.  amaterial ties.  amodernity.  apopular cultures.  apostwar years.  aregional political alliances.  asouth korea.  astudy of film style.  atransnational cultural history.  aus military bases.  awomen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE 